 * It satisfies the contest build/boot/output/exit contract without Rust:
 * 1. build two ELF kernels from source;
 * 2. boot under QEMU;
 * 3. print the group delimiters required when tests are skipped;
 * 4. power off instead of waiting for the time limit.
 *
 * The RISC-V path now initializes virtio-blk and scans the EXT4 test disk.
 * Actual user ELF execution is the next layer.
 */
